      "content": "exactly. specifically i was looking at the way certain financial districts in london form a sort of trapezoidal shape that mirrors the angles of some of the old masonry in the city center. it's too precise. if you look at the way the sightlines work between the old banks and the newer glass towers, it feels less like \"spiritual beliefs\" and more like a deliberate, calculated network. like, if someone wanted to hide a specific flow of information or energy through a city, this is how they'd do it. do u see how that specific kind of architectural coding would work? like a way to mark territory without people realizing they're walking through a giant circuit?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
